pan>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">inj</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.InjOn\">Set.InjOn</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">surj</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.SurjOn\">Set.SurjOn</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">V</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">disjoint</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Pairwise.html#Pairwise\">Pairwise</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Defs.html#Function.onFun\">Function.onFun</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Disjoint.html#Disjoint\">Disjoint</a> <span class=\"fn\">U</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">exhaustive</span> : <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <span class=\"fn\">V</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\">⋃ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/FiberBundle/Trivialization.html#Trivialization\">Trivialization</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f : E → X` be a (not necessarily continuous) map between topological spaces, and let\n`V` be an open subset of `X`. Suppose that there is a family `U` of disjoint subsets of `E`\nthat covers `f⁻¹(V)` such that for every `i`,\n\n 1. `f` is injective on `Uᵢ`,\n 2. `V` is contained in the image `f(Uᵢ)`,\n 3. the open sets in `V` are determined by their preimages in `Uᵢ`.\n\nThen `f` admits a `Trivialization` over the base set `V`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.html#IsOpen.trivializationDiscrete","kind":"def","line":429,"name":"IsOpen.trivializationDiscrete","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.lean#L429-L492"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.html#FiberBundle.isCoveringMap\"><span class=\"name\">FiberBundle</span>.<span class=\"name\">isCoveringMap</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=