> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">I</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">I</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Homeomorph/Defs.html#Homeomorph\">≃ₜ</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.preimage\">⁻¹'</a> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `x : X` is evenly covered by `f` with fiber `I`, then `I` is homeomorphic to `f ⁻¹' {x}`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.html#IsEvenlyCovered.fiberHomeomorph","kind":"def","line":48,"name":"IsEvenlyCovered.fiberHomeomorph","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.lean#L48-L58"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.html#IsEvenlyCovered\"><span class=\"name\">IsEvenlyCovered</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">E</span> → <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">I</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A point `x : X` is evenly covered by `f : E → X` if `x` has an evenly covered neighborhood.\n\n**Remark**: `DiscreteTopology I ∧ ∃ Trivialization I f, x ∈ t.baseSet` would be a simpler\ndefinition, but unfortunately it does not work if `E` is nonempty but nonetheless `f` has empty\nfibers over `s`. If `OpenPartialHomeomorph` could be refactored to work with an empty space and a\nnonempty space while preserving the APIs, we could switch back to the definition. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.html#IsEvenlyCovered","kind":"def","line":34,"name":"IsEvenlyCovered","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Covering/Basic.lean#L34-L42"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.DiscreteSubset","Mathlib.Topology.FiberBundle.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.IsLocalHomeomorph"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Covering.Basic"}